      "content": "It's heartbreaking to see your daughter sacrificing her own life for yours, and it's true that it can be a heavy burden to carry. Stopping the cycle of dependence might be the kindest thing you can do for her - not by giving up, but by finding ways to make your own life more manageable, so she can finally have some space to breathe. It's a selfish act, but it's also a selfless one, in the sense that it's putting her needs before your own.",
      "source": "target",
